The women of uMthwalume stood together in solidarity and in one voice while calling for an end to gender-based violence following the brutal murders of five women whose bodies were discovered in the sugar cane fields recently. Led by the Ugu District deputy mayor, Phumlile Mthiyane and Umzumbe mayor, Londolo Zungu, scores of women gathered at Turton Taxi Rank to say a prayer for slain Nosipho and Akhona Gumede, Nelisiwe Dube, Zama Chiliza and the fifth yet to be identified victim.